sep.gaia.resources.poi

Class POICache

  • java.lang.Object
    • sep.gaia.resources.Cache<PointOfInterest>
      • sep.gaia.resources.poi.POICache

  • public class POICache
extends Cache<PointOfInterest>
    Defines a class for caching Point-Of-Interests (POI) in memory. Besides the limitations for POIs must be equal, cached data will be returned if the bounding-box is equal to or is contained in the one POIs are queried for. This gives advantage if a subset of previously cached POIs of the same category are queried, e.g. if the view is zoomed in.
    Author:
    Max Witzelsperger (Specification: Matthias Fisch)

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public java.util.Collection<PointOfInterest> get(POIQuery query)
        Checks if there are POIs cached for query by two criteria. POI-Data is returned if the limitations of query match those of the prior cached query. Also the bounding-box in query must be contained in or be equal to the bounding-box of the query held in the cache.
        Parameters:
        query - The query defining a bounding-box to search in and conditions to be met.
        Returns:
        The collection of POIs suitable for query or null if no POIs are available or only a subset is cached.

      • addResources

        public void addResources(POIQuery query,
                java.util.Collection<PointOfInterest> pois)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Adds a collection of POIs, identifiable by query, to the cache. Each POI in pois will be checked for equality to a POI already cached and if possible the latter is referenced instead of the one in pois in order to save memory. The use-count of the collection is initially set to zero. Note that the collection as a whole is the entry inserted and not the particular elements of it.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
